== About
I am a research scientist in 
[https://tech.fb.com/ar-vr/ Facebook Reality Labs Research] (FRL Research), 
working on [https://ai.facebook.com/blog/hand-tracking-deep-neural-networks the future of interaction tracking] 
for Virtual Reality and Augmented Reality, 
using computer vision and machine learning techniques. (*/We are looking for interns!/*)

Previously, I earned PhD and MSc degrees in computer science from [www.bu.edu Boston University],  
advised by [http://www.cs.bu.edu/~sclaroff Professor Stan Sclaroff]. 
My PhD dissertation focused on learning vector embeddings for image retrieval and other related computer vision tasks.
During grad school, I did research internships at Disney Research and Honda Research Institute, 
and I was a visiting student at Brown University.
I hold a Bachelor's degree in computer science from Zhejiang University, China. 
\n

== News
- 2019/09: Check out [https://ai.facebook.com/blog/hand-tracking-deep-neural-networks hand tracking on Oculus Quest]!
- 2019/04: "Hashing with Mutual Information" accepted by IEEE TPAMI, and "Generalized Majorization-Minimization" accepted by ICML 2019
- 2019/02: "Deep Metric Learning to Rank" accepted by CVPR 2019! ([https://github.com/kunhe/FastAP-metric-learning code])
- 2018/10: Joined Facebook Reality Labs.
- 2018/10: A paper on "text-to-clip retrieval" accepted by AAAI 2019. 
[https://github.com/VisionLearningGroup/Text-to-Clip_Retrieval Code] is available.
- 2018/07: Defended PhD dissertation.
- 2018/07: "Hashing with Binary Matrix Pursuit" accepted by ECCV 2018.
- 2018/04: Two papers in CVPR 2018: [http://github.com/kunhe/TALR Hashing as Tie-Aware Learning to Rank], 
and [papers/DOAP/index.html Local Descriptors Optimized for Average Precision].
- 2018/01: Paper on predicting foreground segmentation ambiguity accepted by IJCV.
- 2017/07: "MIHash: Online Hashing with Mutual Information" accepted by ICCV 2017. ([https://github.com/fcakir/mihash code])


